# Block Development Workflow

When building a new block, follow these steps in order.

## 1. Define the Content Structure

Decide the authoring contract before writing code. Each row in the authored table becomes a child `<div>` of the block. Each cell becomes a nested `<div>`.

Inspect existing content with `curl http://localhost:3000/path.plain.html` or `console.log(block.innerHTML)` to verify assumptions.

## 2. Create Block Files

Create `blocks/{name}/{name}.js` and `blocks/{name}/{name}.css`.

**JavaScript pattern:**

```js
import { toClassName } from '../../scripts/aem.js';

export default function decorate(block) {
  // 1. Extract data from block.children rows/cells
  // 2. Build new DOM structure with semantic HTML and ARIA attributes
  // 3. Replace or prepend into block
  // 4. Add event listeners
}
```

**CSS rules:**
- Scope all selectors to `.{blockname}` (e.g. `.tabs .tabs-list`)
- Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, `@media (width >= 600px)` and `(width >= 900px)` for larger
- Use project CSS custom properties (`--background-color`, `--text-color`, `--dark-color`, `--light-color`, `--link-color`, `--body-font-size-*`)
- Never use `{blockname}-container` or `{blockname}-wrapper` class names

## 3. Create Test Content

Create `drafts/{name}-test.plain.html` containing only section `<div>` elements (no `<html>`, `<head>`, `<body>`, or `<main>` wrappers). The AEM CLI wraps this content automatically.

```html
<div>
  <h2>Heading for the section</h2>
</div>
<div>
  <div class="{blockname}">
    <div>
      <div>Cell 1</div>
      <div>Cell 2</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

Start the dev server with `--html-folder drafts` and access at `http://localhost:3000/drafts/{name}-test`. The URL **must** include the `/drafts/` prefix.

## 4. Validate

- Run `npm run lint` (ESLint + Stylelint must pass)
- Test in browser: visual rendering, click interactions, keyboard navigation
- Verify accessibility: ARIA roles, focus management, screen reader labels
